The totality of pain and suffering of mankind is simply immeasurable. If we could see spiritual injury as we see physical one, every time we go outside we would witness unbearable sights, all sin is invasive surgery, mutilation, porcelain bullets spreading shrapnel in organs

Like from times when someone revealed their most private struggles, obsessive anxieties, I found out that every single of all persons carries simply immense amount of trauma. The fragile ones, the tough ones, the shallow, the simple, everyone is brutalized by the wages of sin

Even people who seem completely dumb, two-dimensional, they also have a reservoir of poisonous pain leaking into their systems. Strong men are not saved, no one is. There truly is no escape from pain in the psychological/physical domain. It can be well hidden, but it always leaks

Every day we lash at others even in our gentle moments, we are tempted into subtle cruelties, we torture our close ones and the people in the street, power games, punishments, that are always returned, doubled, tripled. We wound until we rot. All of ur pain is a brick in a tower.

And all pain, that was suffered in all times, spread between trillions of men, immeasurable pain, was also suffered by Christ. A Mesopotamian child mocking his little brother, a peasant in China watching his wife die from a disease - all of this was experienced by God as a man

I truly can't even begin to comprehend this. Imagine taking the pain of your closest friends. Maybe you can suffer through the pain of two people, but four? Five? And yet Christ suffered a literal infinity, we really can not comprehend His sacrifice and pain on the Cross
